gomodel:SYNGO_744  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: SV31 actively transports zinc (zn2+) in a proton-dependent manner.\n\nSV31 is able to bind zinc: Recombinant SV31 expression in NGF-differentiated PC12 cells and measurement of zinc binding activity using a cell-permeable zinc indicator FluoZin-3. Comparison of wild-type SV31 and mutated SV31 (putative zinc-binding sites were mutated) revealed significantly reduced zinc-binding capacities for the mutant (Fig.6c).\n\nSV31 is able to transport zinc in a proton-dependent manner (Fig.7): SV31 proteoliposomes acidified to pH 6.0 containing the indicator FluoZin-1 exhibit an accumulation of luminal fluorescence after addition of 100 uM Zn2+. SV31 proteoliposomes at pH 8.0, and proteoliposomes containing mutated SV31 acidified to pH 6.0 do not exhibit an accumulation of fluorescence after zinc application.. Experimental description: ???\nI am guessing \"rat\", because in their first paper I found the following information: The open reading frame of the rat SV31 gene (database accession number XM_341114) was synthesized by Epoch Biolabs...\n\n6/6/2017 Pim\n- Email sent to Walther Volknandt for info on the species of the SV31 protein featured in the paper. The author replied:\n\n\"the species is rat\nBest\nWalter Volknandt\"\n- Species set to *rat* accordingly" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" ;
        dc:date           "2018-01-25" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_744" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

